git-reword (1.0.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix: Commit message rewriting now works correctly by modifying commit.message
    directly in commit callback instead of using message callback with state file
  * Fix: Resolved issue where commit messages were not being replaced due to
    callback execution order (message callback runs before commit callback sets state)

 -- Lenik <git-reword@bodz.net>  Wed, 25 Dec 2024 20:00:00 +0000

git-reword (1.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix: Preserve git remotes during commit message rewriting
  * Fix: Remove --partial flag to fully replace commits instead of mixing old and new history
  * Fix: Ensure git log shows same commit count after rewriting (old commits fully replaced)
  * Improvement: Automatically save and restore remotes before/after filter-repo runs

 -- Lenik (谢继雷) <lenik@bodz.net>  Thu, 25 Dec 2025 11:54:42 +0000

git-reword (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release
  * Add git-reword utility for rewording commit messages
  * Add gentestrepo for generating test repositories
  * Add genrewords for generating reword message directories

 -- Lenik (谢继雷) <lenik@bodz.net>  Wed, 01 Jan 2025 12:00:00 +0000

